    <item>
      <title>My guest Melanie yesterday said “it tastes like a summer morning after rain”. It...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DLcCmw9xBsX/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/513544665_18516730102050087_2918852399493111022_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=110&amp;ig_cache_key=MzY2NDgxNTY0MDc0Mjg5NzkzNQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjE0NDB4MTkyMC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=E_zOn28tGmsQ7kNvwGDjqYJ&amp;_nc_oc=Ado0S1ruOFts3rvGoE9Ldfd3MmrKGGJgUnN4KCHF7ZKTIC0c5PIwsoLjX7oQ2-i3oTw&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=U3t2t_7ojqSC7kB-Yjg7pA&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afxza8z87aVgJxcffMi48KyO_tJqSXGdrE9qx8XnYRzzfA&amp;oe=69C9A691" alt="Instagram billede fra @olaszwalek" /></p><p><strong>@olaszwalek</strong></p><p>My guest Melanie yesterday said “it tastes like a summer morning after rain”. It’s fresh, it’s warm, smells like herb garden. And it’s moist too. Spinach uszka filled with hand-shelled ton of peas and baby fava. Lots of fresh majoram, a big bunch of dill too. Just a bit of garlic, generous black pepper in the filling and on the dumplin when you serve. Fennel butter works insane. (But terragon just always beats it all). I warm up butter aside and pour it over warm dumplings rather than cook them in it. <br/>
<br/>
When making dough- boiling water always, generous splash of oil. Let it rest, keep it slightly sticky, add flour while rolling out. I never use eggs, but I do use soft flour. Babcia works on her dough for 15 minutes- I let my rest and work on it less. Boil just so they swim up +3 minutes.</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/513544665_18516730102050087_2918852399493111022_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=110&amp;ig_cache_key=MzY2NDgxNTY0MDc0Mjg5NzkzNQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjE0NDB4MTkyMC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=E_zOn28tGmsQ7kNvwGDjqYJ&amp;_nc_oc=Ado0S1ruOFts3rvGoE9Ldfd3MmrKGGJgUnN4KCHF7ZKTIC0c5PIwsoLjX7oQ2-i3oTw&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=U3t2t_7ojqSC7kB-Yjg7pA&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afxza8z87aVgJxcffMi48KyO_tJqSXGdrE9qx8XnYRzzfA&amp;oe=69C9A691" alt="Instagram billede fra @olaszwalek" /></p><p><strong>@olaszwalek</strong></p><p>My guest Melanie yesterday said “it tastes like a summer morning after rain”. It’s fresh, it’s warm, smells like herb garden. And it’s moist too. Spinach uszka filled with hand-shelled ton of peas and baby fava. Lots of fresh majoram, a big bunch of dill too. Just a bit of garlic, generous black pepper in the filling and on the dumplin when you serve. Fennel butter works insane. (But terragon just always beats it all). I warm up butter aside and pour it over warm dumplings rather than cook them in it. <br/>
<br/>
When making dough- boiling water always, generous splash of oil. Let it rest, keep it slightly sticky, add flour while rolling out. I never use eggs, but I do use soft flour. Babcia works on her dough for 15 minutes- I let my rest and work on it less. Boil just so they swim up +3 minutes.</p>]]></content:encoded>
